  <programme start="20260418192700 +0000" stop="20260418193900 +0000" channel="dreamworkshd.unifitv">
    <title lang="en">Noddy Toyland Detective</title>
    <desc lang="en">Noddy returns from a Make and Take party at Pat-Pat's and finds the Builders are constructing a big orange palace in Toy Green. by order of the King of Toyland! Noddy decides to investigate: who is the mysterious King of Toyland? He spots the Knights carrying a royal litter, but all he can see inside is the top of an orange crown. Realising the King's favourite colour must be orange, Noddy remembers seeing Pat-Pat painting a bowl of oranges and wonders if she knows who the King is. Pat-Pat doesn't but following the clue of a cut out crown shape in orange card and using his investigative skills Noddy works out that Cloppycorn is the King of Toyland. He was fed up being bossed around by Hoof and Bling so decided to be king for the day with a little help from Queen Sparklewings. Bling and Hoof are sorry for upsetting Noddy and everyone is friends again in time for the Royal Ball! Well done Noddy. Case closed!</desc>
    <category lang="en">Kids</category>
    <episode-num system="xmltv_ns">0.41.</episode-num>
    <episode-num system="onscreen">S1E42</episode-num>
  </programme>
  <programme start="20260418193900 +0000" stop="20260418195100 +0000" channel="dreamworkshd.unifitv">
    <title lang="en">Noddy Toyland Detective</title>
    <desc lang="en">Everyone is decorating special balloons in Toyland. They're going to have a big Balloon Release at the end of the day and see how far they can fly. But when Noddy returns in the afternoon with Big Ears, the balloons have already flown away! Noddy decides to investigate. Following all the clues, he arrives at Deltoid's house. The action hero toy tells him that he only took back his specially decorated balloon. The others were still there earlier. Noddy works out that when Deltoid took his balloon, he retried the strings of the others with a knot that came undone. The balloons are flying away! Revs quickly converts to helicopter mode and Noddy is able to catch the balloons before they fly away for good. Back at Toy Green later, Deltoid is persuaded to release his balloon alongside the other balloons and this time the Balloon Release takes place without any problems at all. Well done Deltoid and well done Noddy!</desc>
    <category lang="en">Kids</category>
    <episode-num system="xmltv_ns">0.42.</episode-num>
    <episode-num system="onscreen">S1E43</episode-num>
  </programme>
  <programme start="20260418195100 +0000" stop="20260418200500 +0000" channel="dreamworkshd.unifitv">
    <title lang="en">Noddy Toyland Detective</title>
    <desc lang="en">Noddy and his friends are building a toy tower. Carlton is joining in and having a great time. They've almost finished when one of the brick pieces goes missing! Oh no. How can they finish the tower without the last brick? Noddy needs to investigate. Using his detecting skills Noddy soon finds the missing brick. But when he gets back to the Toy Green to finish the tower, he discovers that another brick has gone missing! What's going on? This investigation is really complicated! Noddy works out that the bricks were taken by Carlton. The big cat admits that he was having so much fun playing that he didn't want the game to end! Everyone forgives him and they decide to carry on playing all afternoon, all thanks to Noddy! Well done!</desc>
